metadata.name: Composizione Semplice #236
metadata.description:
Simple things.
Life is full of them.
Don't let them pass.
Embrace them.
Observe them.
Be present.
Be curious.
Be aware.

Press 's' to save the current view of the artwork.

Artwork made with p5js.

metadata.name: Miniscapes #384
metadata.description:
Miniscapes merges generative code (Rich's bit) with meticulously designed scenes and elements (Rick's bit), to create minimalist landscapes intended to charm, delight, and surprise.

Our aim was to convey as much as possible with as little as possible by using simple shapes and lines to represent a wide variety of natural landscapes.

We hope that you find as much joy in owning a Miniscape as we did in creating them.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [p] to pause an animated output
- Press [r] to reset an animated output (this will also pause)

metadata.name: Pobbles #232
metadata.description:
The pobbles are generative blob-rocks: staring in silence, sometimes half-smiling, generally bored. 

â€¢ The pobbles are digital recreations of a series of rock-doodles by S.F.Kislev (my big brother). They are an attempt to capture a specific, singular handwriting, and evolve it using code. 
â€¢ See the original, 2014 handmade version here - https://pobbles.tez.page..
â€¢ Alternative titles considered include Pegglesâ„¢, Plopsâ„¢, Blobbiesâ„¢, Floofsâ„¢, Flintstonesâ„¢, Lardiesâ„¢, Plumpsâ„¢, Fatsâ„¢ and Wet-Onesâ„¢. 
â€¢ The pobbles are written entirely in paper.js and p5.js. 
â€¢ The pobbles are an effort to take generative art into the realm of the cute. 
â€¢ They work well with toddlers.

metadata.name: Bamboo and Beyond #48
metadata.description:
The idea was inspired by Japanese paintings that always express peace and tranquility.

Without using any images and only using programming knowledge, each mint is tried to be a unique and relaxing work of art. â€œBamboo and Beyondâ€ is an exploration to find harmony and calm in a work of art with a minimal style. each bamboo has a unique structure that creates a minimal work of art with a variety of color palettes, arrangements and leaves.

Press â€™sâ€™ on the live mode to save the artwork.
Made with P5js.

metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #360
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.

metadata.name: Cables and Clouds #6
metadata.description:
Capturing clouds... an old dream of mad scientist... coming true...
But wait... are they real clouds ? Maybe... maybe not...
Is it the real life ?
Is this just fantasy ?

Interaction.
Press h in live mode to list the possibilities.
Key 's'  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key 'c' to change color palette
Key 'd' to toggle a special color mode to highlight the different components (and have the number of points used in your specific drawing).

Features.
18 different features displayed (format, color palettes, main elements characteristics, rare elements...).

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #330
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. â€œThe Bugged Treeâ€â€™s code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations arenâ€™t under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as thereâ€™s a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Connected #124
metadata.description:
An artistic version of the travelling salesperson problem.
In this particle system, each particle has to visit a complete set of attractors.
The path of each particle is then plotted, resulting in unique abstract geometries.


Artist: Estienne
Made with p5.js
Dec 2021
